      "comment_id" : 51576906,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "Instead of using an &#39;Qualifier&#39; annotation in some cases it is may be preferable to use name of field as sort of qualifier. For example, if you have defined two beans of type A named &#39;a1&#39; and &#39;a2&#39; respectively, in your component you can define field &#39;@Autowired A a1;&#39; instead of &#39;@Autowired @Qualifier(&quot;a1&quot;) a;&#39;. <a href=\"http://docs.spring.io/spring/docs/current/spring-framework-reference/htmlsingle/#beans-autowired-annotation-qualifiers\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">See reference: &#39;For a fallback match, the bean name is considered a default qualifier value.&#39;</a>"
    }, {
